definition.value: Trianion of 2-cis,6-trans-farnesyl diphosphate arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A S-acylglutathione in which the acyl group specified is formyl.
An  azaarene comprising a benzene core in which one -CH group is replaced by a nitrogen atom. It is the parent compound of the class pyridines.
A  non-proteinogenic alpha-amino acid that is glycine substituted by two alkyl groups at position 2.
